HEADWORD: Acetate
<hw>Ac"e*tate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acetum</ets> vinegar, fr. <ets>acere</ets> to be sour.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A salt formed by the union of acetic acid with a
base or positive radical; <as>as, <ex>acetate</ex> of lead,
<ex>acetate</ex> of potash</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acetated</ent>⟦br⟧
